The show predominantly - Promoolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. title: Bhogi kundalu muggulu designs by Suneetha || Sankranthi /Pongal kolam || new rangoli
tags: rangoli,rangoli designs,kolam,kolam designs,muggulu,muggulu designs,rangoli with dots,rangoli designs with dots,easy rangoli,easy rangoli designs,rangoli art,rangoli art designs,rangoli kolam,kolam rangoli,kolam with dots,kolam designs with dots,simple kolam,padi kolam,easy kolam,muggulu with dots,muggulu designs with dots,chukkala muggulu,designs with dots,how to draw,latest rangoli,indian rangoli,Bhogi kundalu muggulu,Sankranthi,pongal rangoli
description: It is our tradition to draw kolam every day morning at the door steps.There are many benifits of drawing kolam in front of the house.It is auspecious and believes Godess Lakshmi enters the house if kolam is drawn.Kolam brings lot of positive vibrations and energy to you and your home.Draw kolam soon after you wake up and then do your prayers.Kolam or rangoli is a part of Indian culture and transferred from generation to next generation.This ancient art form is also called as muggulu in parts  of South India like Andhra pradesh and Telangana.People draw different creative rangoli kolam designs using kolam powder or muggu pindi which is actually crushed Lime stone powder available at different parts of India.There are different types of rangoli or kolam designs like dots kolam, sikku kolam, padi kolam, Margazhi kolam.People draw special rangoli designs for Festivals like Sankranthi (Pongal), Diwali (Deepavali), Vijaya dasami (Dasara).Women create deepam rangoli or kolam designs during diwali festival time, create very big and Dhanurmasam muggulu (Margazhi) for Sankranthi or Pongal festival.It is a belief among the people that drawing muggulu infront of the house in the early morning soon after wake bringsgood fortune to them and their family.People mix rice flour to lime stone powder and prepare their own kolam powder. Muggulu can also be drawn with rice flour only.These Beautiful and creative designs are decorated with flowers based on the occasion or festival.

description: PERFECT WAYS TO REUSE ORDINARY THINGSRed lipstick makes you feel glamorous but it‚Äôs hard to prevent your lipstick from getting smudged while eating. We have a perfect solution ‚Äì mix some peel-off mask with red food coloring. Apply the mixture on your lips using a lip brush. Let dry and remove. Now you have perfect red lips!Rubber bands are super multifunctional items you can use everywhere. Place a rubber band on top of a paint can to remove the excess paint from the brush. Use rubber bands and a plastic container to make a perfect organizer for mascara and lipsticks of different colors. If eyeglasses tend to slip off your nose, take a couple of rubber bands and watch our tutorial!If you have a magnetic sheet at home, you should watch our video to find out unusual ways to use it:-Stick magnetic sheet to your mop to find small metal items like safety pins on the floor-Use magnet sheet instead of sticky tape to hang posters-Organize tiny items in your drawer. Glue a small magnet to the bottom of a small saucer you like-Use magnetic stripe to store toothbrushes in the bathroomNeed a door stopper? We have a brilliant idea how to make a cool door stopper that will amaze your family. description: Union cabinet on Monday approved 10% reservation in jobs and educational institutions for economically weak sections in general category. This will be given over and above the existing 50% reservation. In this video, I will tell you why I think this new scheme is nothing but a Jumla and a Lollipop to appease voters. The data suggests that more than 90% of general category people are eligible for being ‚ÄòEconomically weak‚Äù and poor according to new criterion (based on my assumptions). So the question arises here, will the real poor people even benefit from this? What is the point of this new reservation? Ironically, people sill have to pay income tax despite being eligible under this category. description: Besan barfi recipe, Besan Til Ki Barfi Recipe, gramflour barfi recipe, besan ki burfi, Ingredients of Til Magad BarfiChickpea Flour - 1 cup (110 gms)Sesame Seeds - 3/4 cup (110 gms)Ghee - 1/2 cup (110 gms)Mawa - 1 cup (200 gms)Sugar - 1.25 cups (200 gms)Almond Flakes - 1/4 cup Green Cardamom Powder - 1 Tsp How to make Til Magad Barfi1- Take ¬æ cup of sesame seeds in a bowl and dry roast them in a pan while continuously stirring them.2- The sesame seeds have expanded and their colour has changed because they have roasted.3-  Grind them in a mixer after cooling them.4-  Melt ¬Ω cup of Ghee in a pan and add 1 cup of chickpea flour to it. 5- Cook the chickpea flour while continuously stirring them on the medium flame.6- Roast until its colour changes and soothing fragrance appears.7- Add 1 cup of crumbled Mawa to it on the low flame.8- Cook again while continuously stirring it for 10 minutes. 9- Add 1.25 cups of powdered sugar and mix them properly.10- Add the ground sesame seeds along with 1 tsp of green cardamom powder to it on the low flame.11- Stir and roast all the ingredients well on the low flame.12- Grease a tray using Ghee to set the Barfi.13- Spread the mixture evenly on the plate.14- Garnish it with almond flakes and press them using a spatula to insert in it.15- Place it beneath the fan or at a cool place to set for an hour.16- Cut the pieces into your desired size.17- Heat the tray while rotating it over the flame.18- Separate the pieces and serve them.Serving:1- Store it in an airtight container inside the refrigerator and consume it for 10-12 days. Generally it is made on Makar Sankranti. Tilachi vadi is made using sesame seeds i.e. til and gudh. This is very easy and simple recipe. Do try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. You also can like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 3/4 cup White sesame seeds‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup Regular Gudh / Light jaggery‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup Chickkicha gudh / Dark jaggery‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup grated dry Coconut‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup Roasted peanut powder‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp Cardamom powder‚Ä¢ A little Nutmeg powder‚Ä¢ GheeMethod:‚Ä¢ Heat up a pan on low to medium heat. ‚Ä¢ Add sesame seeds and roast until these get light golden color. ‚Ä¢ Roast on low to medium heat only. Stir continuously while   roasting. ‚Ä¢ Transfer the roasted sesame seeds into a plate. ‚Ä¢ You can roast coconut too if you want. ‚Ä¢ In another pan, heat up ghee. ‚Ä¢ Add light jaggery and dark jaggery. ‚Ä¢ Mix well and let the gudh melt well. ‚Ä¢ Small pieces of gudh should melt and gudh also should melt well. ‚Ä¢ No need make syrup. Just make sure gudh is melted well. ‚Ä¢ Add roasted sesame seeds, dry coconut, roasted peanut powder,   cardamom powder, nutmeg powder and mix well quickly. ‚Ä¢ Take a steel plate and spread some ghee on it. ‚Ä¢ Transfer the mixture into the dish when hot and spread it well. ‚Ä¢ Sprinkle dry coconut for garnishing and let the mixture cool down   a little.‚Ä¢ Do not let the mixture cool down completely. ‚Ä¢ When the mixture cools down a little cut it into pieces. ‚Ä¢ Tilachi vadi is already.Subscribe to my other channelsMadharasrecipehttp://www.youtube.com/c/madhurasrecipe?sub_confirmation=1Hindi channelhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCIdtPLjTb111r4iubQ9Mq5A?sub_confirmation=1For some More Recipes‡§π‡§æ‡§§‡§æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ö‡§ü‡§ï‡•á ‡§® ‡§¶‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§µ‡§≥‡§æ ‡§§‡§ø‡§≥‡§æ‡§ö‡•á ‡§≤‡§æ‡§°‡•Ç | How to make Til Ladoo | Til Ladoo | MadhurasRecipe | Ep - The company that makes flexible displays has unveiled the FlexPai foldable display smartphone. It's an Android smartphone that has a 7.8-inch display that folds to act as a phone or tablet, whenever required. Along with the interesting foldable display, the FlexPai also packs in powerful specifications under the hood.It is powered by Qualcomm's new Snapdragon 855 octa-core processor coupled with 6/8GB of RAM and 128/256GB of onboard storage respectively. The FlexPai also features dual cameras ‚Äî 16MP+20MP with an aperture f/1.8. A 3970mAh battery powers foldable FlexPai smartphone and also supports quick charging.
